This provides a a proxy class iCubLimbIF which serves as an interface to the
iCub limbs through YARP. Follow the following steps to make your own iCub limb
module in IQR:

1) cmake and compile in the subdirectory yarpIFlib to create the library
2) set the environment variable YARPIFLIB_DIR and YARPIFLIB_INCLUDE_DIRS to
the path of the above subdirectory
3) compile your own module (for any limb) as shown in the example provided in
subdirectory iqrNeckModule


<< Caution: avoid setting the joints directly! The example should serve just
as a proof of concept >>

-----have fun

Zenon Mathews & Ugo Pattacini 23 Sep 2009
